# Cursor Rules for matteokuberek.com

## File Naming Conventions

- All file names MUST be lowercase with hyphens for separation
- Example: `hero-section.tsx`, `contact-form.tsx`
- Exceptions: README.md, LICENSE, .env files, and configuration files that require specific casing
- Component files: `component-name.tsx`
- Documentation files: `document-name.md` in `/docs` folder
- Type definition files: `type-name.ts` in `/src/types` folder

## Component Structure

- All components in `/src/app/components/`
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Always define prop interfaces
- Use `'use client'` directive when client-side features needed
- One component per file
- Export components as named exports: `export const ComponentName`

### Component Template

```typescript
'use client';

import React from 'react';

interface ComponentNameProps {
  title?: string;
  // Define all props with types
}

export const ComponentName: React.FC<ComponentNameProps> = ({ title }) => {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Component JSX */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## TypeScript Standards

- Strict mode enabled
- Always define types/interfaces
- No `any` types unless absolutely necessary
- Use proper type inference
- Define prop interfaces for all components
- Use type aliases for complex types

## Styling Guidelines

- Primary: Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use semantic class names when needed
- Responsive design: mobile-first approach
- Global styles only in `globals.css`
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Follow design system colors and tokens

## Code Quality

- Clean, readable code
- Self-documenting code preferred
- Comments only for complex logic
- Remove console.logs before commit
- No unused imports or variables
- Proper error handling
- Use early returns to reduce nesting

